  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "What is الاسم المقصور?",
      "titleArabic": "تعريف الاسم المقصور",
      "content": [
        "الاسم المقصور is a noun ending in an unchangeable alif (ا or ى), like فَتًى (young man), هُدًى (guidance), and عَصَا (stick).",
        "The alif cannot change, so all case endings (damma, fatha, kasra) are estimated on it."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Ends in alif that cannot take vowels",
        "Can end in ى (الفَتَى) or ا (العَصَا)",
        "All case endings are muqaddara (estimated)",
        "Common examples: الفَتَى، الهُدَى، المُصْطَفَى، الدُّنْيَا"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ الْفَتَى", "english": "The young man came (nominative estimated)" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ الْفَتَى", "english": "I saw the young man (accusative estimated)" },
        { "arabic": "مَرَرْتُ بِالْفَتَى", "english": "I passed by the young man (genitive estimated)" },
        { "arabic": "الْهُدَى مِنَ اللهِ", "english": "Guidance is from Allah" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Dual and Plural of المقصور",
      "titleArabic": "تثنية وجمع المقصور",
      "content": [
        "When forming the dual, the alif changes to ي (فَتَيَانِ). For the sound masculine plural, the alif is dropped (مُصْطَفَوْنَ).",
        "The sound feminine plural keeps the alif changed to a fatha before ات (فَتَيَاتٌ)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Dual: الفَتَى → فَتَيَانِ/فَتَيَيْنِ",
        "Sound masculine plural: المُصْطَفَى → المُصْطَفَوْنَ",
        "Sound feminine plural: فَتَاةٌ → فَتَيَاتٌ",
        "The original alif often appears as ya in derivations"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ فَتَيَانِ", "english": "Two young men came" },
        { "arabic": "رَأَيْتُ فَتَيَيْنِ", "english": "I saw two young men" },
        { "arabic": "الْمُصْطَفَوْنَ هُمُ الصَّالِحُونَ", "english": "The chosen ones are the righteous" },
        { "arabic": "الدُّنْيَا فَانِيَةٌ", "english": "The worldly life is temporary" }
      ]
    }
  ],
